12. Summary

The Neural–Spatial Bridge provides the missing architectural layer enabling IWDS to convert generative AI outputs into persistent, navigable simulation objects.

Its primary function is to preserve meaning as world objects transition between:
	•	language
	•	neural representation
	•	spatial runtime
	•	perceptual rendering

By maintaining identity and invariants across these transformations, the NSB enables the IWDS vision of conversationally directed living worlds.

